    "has_raw_measurements": true,
    "raw_measurement_details": "Yes. The platform stores raw experimental files directly from instruments without correction. For RHEED, raw images are saved as .png and videos as .mp4; for PL/Raman mapping, raw spectra are stored as .txt files. The paper also mentions associated AFM images and XPS for some samples, but the main platform datasets described are RHEED and PL/Raman.",
    "has_processed_plots": true,
    "processed_plot_details": "Yes. The platform generates parsed metadata tables, RHEED line profiles extracted along user-defined guidelines, stacked RHEED images from videos, PL/Raman intensity maps, histograms, and fitted parameter maps (maximum intensity, peak position, FWHM). It also provides super-resolution outputs for PL/Raman mapping and ML-derived analyses such as PCA/K-means for RHEED.",
    "dataset_characterization": {
      "data_availability_statement": "All datasets are available on the web platform https://2DMat.ChemDX.org (DOI: 10.23218/2dmat.chemdx). Users can preview datasets with integrated visualization tools before downloading raw data and corresponding metadata. The data is licensed under CC-BY 4.0, and contributed data is owned by the respective contributors. Machine-learning toolkit source code is available on GitHub repositories linked from the toolkit page.",
      "data_provided_types": [
        "raw",
        "processed",
        "scripts"
      ],
      "raw_data_description": "Raw measurement files are uploaded unchanged except for filename tags. RHEED data are .png images and .mp4 videos with '_rheed' in the filename and timestep information for image sequences; PL/Raman mapping data are .txt files with '_pl-pos' or '_raman-pos' tags. The platform also stores metadata and experimental parameters in .xlsx spreadsheets. The paper states that raw data are uploaded without corrections and that the parsing system does not alter the file contents.",
      "processed_data_description": "Processed data include parsed metadata tables, standardized JSON-type data for further processing, extracted RHEED line profiles, stacked RHEED images, PL/Raman fitted spectra and parameter maps, histograms, and super-resolution reconstructed mapping data. The parsing modules convert raw files into a standardized readable format for web visualization.",
      "figure_data_description": "Yes, figure-specific processed data are clearly provided through the platform visualization outputs, especially for RHEED and PL/Raman examples. However, the paper does not explicitly state that separate per-figure source-data files are deposited; instead, the platform provides downloadable raw data and metadata, plus interactive visualizations and derived analysis outputs.",
      "scripts_description": "Yes. The machine learning toolkits are provided as source code in GitHub repositories, and the parsing/visualization pipeline is implemented with built-in Python modules. The ML toolkits are not run directly on the web UI; users download the code and examples for local use.",
      "data_organization": "Mixed, platform-based organization by data group (DATA-UOS and DATA-POSTECH), sample ID, and measurement type. Upload relies on filename tags and spreadsheet metadata; the platform stores data in MongoDB and presents parsed tables and interactive plots.",
      "replot_ready_data_present": true,
      "replot_reason": "The platform provides downloadable raw files plus corresponding metadata, and the visualization tools expose the processed quantities used in the figures. This is sufficient for replotting many displayed analyses, although some ML outputs and interactive transformations may require the external GitHub code.",
      "notes": "The parsing system is intentionally non-destructive: it checks schema/valid values for visualization but does not modify or validate the intrinsic correctness of the data. The paper emphasizes that users should only rename files during upload. Most of the public dataset is experimental and sample-centered rather than figure-centered. The platform currently focuses on two groups: DATA-UOS (in situ RHEED during MBE growth of transition metal chalcogenides) and DATA-POSTECH (PL/Raman mapping of exfoliated and CVD-grown TMDs)."
    },
